summary: This document contains corporate resolutions authorizing Deutsche Bank Trust Company Americas to manage various accounts for a corporation. It outlines the powers granted to authorized signers and the responsibilities of the bank in relation to these accounts.
keyFacts: The document is a Certificate of Corporate Resolutions for a corporation authorizing Deutsche Bank Trust Company Americas as a depositary and investment advisor.
It specifies the powers of Authorized Signers to manage accounts and execute agreements on behalf of the corporation.
The document states that the bank may rely on the instructions of the Authorized Signers unless notified otherwise.
It confirms that no one other than the corporation has any interest in the accounts opened in its name.
The document emphasizes that previous authorities granted to any Authorized Signer not named in this document are revoked.
